IPFS is a peer-to-peer protocol for storing and sharing files in a distributed file system.
Instead of using a centralized server, IPFS uses a content-addressed system, where files are accessed via their hash.

üõ†Ô∏è 1. Installing IPFS
Step 1: Go to the official IPFS download page.
Step 2: Download the Go-IPFS binary for your OS.
Step 3: Extract and install:

tar -xvzf go-ipfs_vX.X.X_linux-amd64.tar.gz
cd go-ipfs
sudo bash install.sh
